description: The confusion stems from the studio's origin story and the linguistic journey the word "Ghibli" has taken. Initially, "Ghibli" (ギブリ) comes from an Italian word pronounced with a hard "G" (as in "gift"). This Italian word means a hot wind from the Sahara Desert, symbolic of the studio's intent to introduce fresh, new winds into the animation industry. Miyazaki, who has a profound fascination with aviation, specifically named the studio after the Italian Caproni Ca.309 Ghibli aircraft. This historical aircraft also carried the Italian pronunciation, solidifying the hard "G" sound.
title: 'Ghibli' or 'Jibli'? The correct way to pronounce it

While his engagements were postponed, he has returned to Clarence House and remains positive about his recovery. The King’s diagnosis was announced in Feb. 2024, and he has continued to maintain a busy schedule despite his condition.
title: King Charles III hospitalised due to cancer treatment side effects

description: Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney has announced a significant shift in the country's relationship with the US, emphasizing the need for economic independence from its neighbour. This comes in response to US tariffs that Carney described as a "direct attack" on Canada's economy, pledging forceful retaliatory measures.
title: Amid tension over tariffs, Canada says 'old relationship' with US is over

description: Mohanlal's sequel 'L2: Empuraan' directed by Prithviraj Sukumaran opened powerfully, earning Rs 22 crore across all languages on its first day. The film collected Rs 19.45 crore in Malayalam, with significant success in Kerala's key cities. It received positive reviews for its high production values and narrative, despite a slower second half. ETimes rated it 3.5 out of 5, noting engaging elements but lacking the novelty and punch of its predecessor 'Lucifer'. The movie, however, retains anticipation with fans eager for more.
title: ‘L2: Empuraan’ box office: Mohanlal starrer opens strong with Rs 22 crore

description: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) has arrested a Delhi Police head constable and a constable for taking a bribe of Rs 2.5 lakh from a complainant. They had demanded Rs 5 lakh to not implicate the complainant in a drug case. The SHO has been suspended.
title: Caught red-handed: CBI nabs 2 cops taking Rs 2.5L

description: Jailed MP Abdul Rashid Sheikh, imprisoned under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act, has approached Delhi High Court seeking relief from paying Rs 1.45 lakh a day for transportation and security arrangements while attending the Parliament session. Rashid, who won the Baramulla seat from prison, argues that the costs imposed are excessive and beyond his financial capacity.
title: Each Parliament visit to cost Rs 1.5L, Engineer Rashid seeks waiver

description: Vikas Namdev, a 26-year-old from Madhya Pradesh, funded his lavish lifestyle through theft. He was apprehended by Vadodara police for stealing gold ornaments worth Rs 34 lakh from female passengers on trains between Vadodara and Surat. Namdev posed as a textile businessman to avoid suspicion.
title: Thief flew to Kolkata for rasgullas, Goa for scotch, caught in Gujarat
